page.content: Canadian pond weed,water parsnip and meadow sweet.Many trees of various sizes marked the course of the stream,namely oak,elder,hazel,alder,elm,sycamore,hor se chestnut,willow,mountain ash and holly.Other plants found in close proximity were ferns,stinging nettles and brambles. Fauna:Equipped with nets,specimen tubes etc.,the investigating party walked up stream.Stones were tuned over and their underside examined for animal life.Creatures found under such stones and in the main stream were:leech,river limpet,water hog louse,hump-backed may-fly nymph,caddis fly larva,mussels,water beetle,water spider,water boatman,sticklebacks and brown trout.
